&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 5 VULNERABLE GROUPS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A rare and exciting opportunity to join the Vulnerable Groups Team in the East area of BCU, as a Community Staff Nurse. We are seeking a highly motivated Registered Nurse to work with families and individuals seeking asylum, refugees and families within the Syrian resettlement programme.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The individual needs to be committed to improving the health outcomes for this client group, working closely with the Health Visitor and through developing and maintaining joint working partnerships with statutory and voluntary agencies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The staff nurse will be responsible for completing the initial health assessments of new individuals and families, in order to identify health needs, address unmet needs, and empower clients to be responsible for their health and well-being.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Effective communication skills are essential for this role to ensure nurse-client relationships are developed and maintained, in order to address barriers to accessing health care. This will include the use of language line and face to face interpretation services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The public health agenda is core to this role and the individual will be responsible for health promotion, including immunisation programme delivery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 17 November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
